<a name="wp1161197"> </a><h3 class="pHeading2">
Establishing Communication Between a PC and a DSC100 Controller
</h3>
<hr />

<a name="wp1161200"> </a><p class="pBody">
This procedure explains how to establish communication between a PC and a DSC100 controller. You can establish communication with serial port or Ethernet port.
</p>
<a name="wp1161201"></a><p class="pBody">
The PC and the Controller must be connected and communicating for you to send and retrieve configuration settings, or trend real-time data of the Controller. 
</p>
<br>

<a name="wp1161202"></a><p class="pBody"><b class="cBold">
Serial Port Communication
</b></p>

<a name="wp1161205"> </a><h5 class="plistHeading">
Procedure
</h5>
<div class="pSmartList1"><ol type="1" class="pSmartList1">
<a name="wp1161206"> </a><div class="pSmartList1"><li> Connect one end of the configuration cable (RS-485 serial communication cable) to COM1/2 on the DSC100 termination panel. </li></div>
<a name="wp1161207"> </a><div class="pSmartList1"><li> Connect the other end of the cable to a serial port on the back of the PC. </li></div>
<a name="wp1161208"> </a><div class="pSmartList1"><li> Click the Start button, point to Programs, and then click DSC100 Configurator. The DSC100 Configurator starts. </li></div>
<a name="wp1161209"> </a><div class="pSmartList1"><li> On the Device menu, click Select Modbus Type command to select communication protocol: Modbus Serial. </li></div>
<a name="wp1161210"> </a><p class="pListIndent"><img src="images/3_Installation-Select_Serial.png" height="239" width="246" border="0" hspace="0" vspace="0"/></p>
<a name="wp1161211"> </a><div class="pSmartList1"><li> On the Device menu, click Comm Settings. </li></div>
<a name="wp1161213"> </a><div class="pSmartList1"><li> On the PC Configurator Comm Settings screen, select a COM port that is available on the PC. Configure the parameters in the PC Configuration Comm Settings screen to match the Comm settings of the Controller.  </li></div>
<a name="wp1161215"> </a><p class="pListIndent"><img src="images/3_Installation-Comm_Settings.png" height="362" width="278" border="0" hspace="0" vspace="0"/></p>
<a name="wp1161216"> </a><div class="pSmartList1"><li> On the Modbus Comm Settings screen, click Test. If communication is established, the message "Success!" appears.  </li></div>
<a name="wp1161217"> </a><div class="pSmartList1"><li> If the message &quot;Success!&quot; does not appear:</li></div>
<ul class="plistBullet"><a name="wp1161221"> </a><div class="plistBullet"><li>Ensure you selected a COM port that is available on the PC.</li></div>
<a name="wp1161218"> </a><div class="plistBullet"><li> Check the configuration cable connections.</li></div>
<a name="wp1183619"> </a><div class="plistBullet"><li> Ensure the parameters in the PC Configurator Comm. Settings match the Comm settings of the DSC100 Controller.</li></div>
</ul><a name="wp1161220"> </a><div class="pSmartList1"><li>After you successfully establish communication, click Connect to DSC100 on the Device menu. </li></div>
</ol></div>


<a name="wp1161230"></a><p class="pBody"><b class="cBold">
Ethernet Port Communication
</b></p>

<a name="wp1161234"> </a><h5 class="plistHeading">
Procedure
</h5>
<div class="pSmartList1"><ol type="1" class="pSmartList1">
<a name="wp1161235"> </a><div class="pSmartList1"><li> Connect one end of the Network Cable to the network interface on the DSC100 termination panel. </li></div>
<a name="wp1161245"> </a><div class="pSmartList1"><li> Connect the other end of the cable to a network interface on the back of the PC. </li></div>
<a name="wp1161236"> </a><div class="pSmartList1"><li> Click the Start button, point to Programs, and then click DSC100 Configurator. The DSC100 Configurator starts. </li></div>
<a name="wp1161237"> </a><div class="pSmartList1"><li> On the Device menu, click Select Modbus Type command to select communication protocol: Modbus Tcp.  </li></div>
<a name="wp1161238"> </a><div class="pSmartList1"><li> On the Device menu click Modbus Tcp Settings.  </li></div>
<a name="wp1161239"> </a><p class="pListIndent"><img src="images/3_Installation-Tcp_Settings.png" height="322" width="735" border="0" hspace="0" vspace="0"/></p>
<a name="wp1161240"> </a><div class="pSmartList1"><li> Configure the Tcp Settings according to the TCP/IP settings of the DSC100 Controller, and you may need to change your PC's TCP/IP Settings to make sure that your PC and DSC100 Controller's IP are in the same Network segment. </li></div>
<a name="wp1161241"> </a><div class="pSmartList1"><li> Click Connect to DSC100 on the Device menu. If fail, the message "ModbusTcp: Unable to connect to DSC100 Controller" will appears: </li></div>
<ul class="plistBullet">
<a name="wp1161242"> </a><div class="plistBullet"><li> Check the configuration cable connections. </li></div>
<a name="wp1161243"> </a><div class="plistBullet"><li> Ensure the parameters in the Modbus Tcp Settings match the TCP/IP settings of the DSC100 Controller. </li></div>
<a name="wp1161244"> </a><div class="plistBullet"><li> Ensure your PC and DSC100 Controller's IP are in the same Network segment. </li></div>
</ul>
</ol></div>

